Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper discusses using CHR as a grammar formalism for natural language processing tasks such as anaphora resolution and text interpretation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper mentions dynamic hypothesis generation techniques, which are commonly used in AI. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper discusses bottom-up parsing, which is a common technique in machine learning for natural language processing. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as CHR is a programming language extension. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper discusses the efficiency and robustness of the parsers implemented using CHR.
